item.title: Repackaging Delta error[317]
item.dc:creator: @itai itai
item.description:
@itai wrote:

[quote=“deathschaos9, post:10, topic:365279”][quote author=itai link=topic=461482.msg3376139#msg3376139 date=1287620489]

But I don’t think java.lang.Object needs to be imported at all.

So I can just remove those imports?

Rather than importing

import com.nova.world.*;

You should use

import com.nova.world.Object;

Why?
[/quote]
Because Java doesn’t know if you want to use Object class from con.nova.world or from java.lang. (and it will fix your errors :|)[/quote]
Just wanted to know so I don’t do same mistake again.
I finally got all my errors fixed.
Thanks!

item.title: Repackaging Delta error[317]
item.dc:creator: @deathschaos9 DeathsChaos9
item.description:
@deathschaos9 wrote:

You have classes called Process and Object in your source, as well as imports of classes also named Process and Object. To fix this, import one of the classes and use the full package name for the other.

For example, your first error.

Rather than having

import com.nova.world.Object; import java.lang.Object;
and

public static ArrayList<Object> objects = new ArrayList<Object>();

You could have

import com.nova.world.Object;
and

public static ArrayList<java.lang.Object> objects = new ArrayList<java.lang.Object>();

Do you understand that? I’m not always good at explaining things.
